/*
Problem: Remove duplicates from a sorted array

Pattern: Two Pointers

Difficulty: Easy

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

-Key Idea:

 i = index of last unique element found // i=0; 

 j = current element being checked // j=1;

- used a while loop (j<n) // where n is the length of the given sorted array

- If nums[i] != nums[j]; // new unique element is found
- Then move i forward. // i++; 
Place it at:
    nums[i+1] = nums[j]; 

Then move j forward. // j++ 

At the end:
    Number of unique elements = i + 1

/*
Learnings:
- Two Pointer pattern works efficiently on sorted arrays.
- also for reducing space! 
*/
*/
